headline: T-Mobile CEO talks cellphone pricing, new Starlink service
summary: T-Mobile (TMUS) is rolling out satellite coverage nationwide on July 23. T-Mobile CEO Mike Sievert speaks with Yahoo Finance Executive Editor Brian Sozzi to address rumors that he's stepping down early, explain how the new T-Satellite service aims to end dead zones for just $10 a month, and discuss the outlook for cellphone costs. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid here.

headline: T-Mobile Partners With Elon Musk's SpaceX To Roll Out Satellite Data Service
summary: T-Mobile US (NASDAQ:TMUS) is looking to launch a new data service on its satellite-to-cell network, powered by SpaceX’s Starlink, by October. T-Satellite, T-Mobile’s satellite-to-cell network service, will commercially launch on July 23. It will offer SMS texting, MMS, picture messaging, and short audio clips.
